<TITLE> India 243 all out, Tendulkar 105 not out </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 18 (bdnews24.com)  Sachin Tendulkar reached his 44th Test hundred after play resumed on the second day of the first Test between Bangladesh and India at the Zohur Ahmed Chowdhury Stadium in Chittagong on Monday. India, who began on 213-8 in their first innings, were all out for 243 in 70.5 overs. Tendulkar remained unbeaten on 105 off 166 balls with 11 fours and two sixes. Shahadat Hossain and Shakib Al Hasan grabbed five wickets 
